tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows a markedly low HbA1c, which may suggest recent hypoglycemia, anemia, or altered red cell turnover; clinical correlation is advised. All other parameters are within normal limits except for mildly decreased total CO₂, which may indicate mild metabolic acidosis or compensated respiratory alkalosis. No acute renal or electrolyte disturbances are evident.
